_:f0482b0508cfcd935283d986565edff0 a <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E52_Time-span> ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "a martyr 'star of Syria', commemorated on 13 Yakkātit. According to his commemoration in Synaxarion, he was a son of a governor of Syria and had a sister Eulophia. Having chosen monastic life, he refused to bed the wife of a king of Syria, who was so furious that ordered him to be tortured and accused him of being a sorcerer in front of the king, who had Eusebius beheaded. He was then reportedly resurrected by the archangels Michael, Gabriel, and Uriel. " .
